parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator/transmission cooler can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power
stalling
or difficulty shifting gears. The transmission may slip or hesitate
and the vehicle may produce a loud noise or vibration. The coolant and transmission fluid may mix
causing damage to the transmission and radiator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in running out of fuel while driving, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays incorrect fuel levels
the fuel gauge fluctuates between empty and full
the "Service Engine Soon" or "Check Engine" light illuminates
the vehicle runs out of fuel despite the gauge showing a quarter tank or more
and the fuel gauge does not update after refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause a loss of motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
and the transmission fluid cooler fails
causing contamination of the transmission fluid and damage to internal transmission components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant to leak into the transmission, leading to transmission failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a rough vibration when shifting gears
the transmission may slip or hesitate
the engine may overheat
and the vehicle may eventually stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Due to Radiator Coolant Contamination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The contamination of the transmission with radiator coolant can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a rough vibration when shifting gears
the transmission may slip or hesitate
the engine may overheat
and the vehicle may eventually stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Notification of Known Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of notification of a known defect can lead to unexpected transmission failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a sudden loss of power
the transmission may slip or hesitate
and the vehicle may eventually stall or fail to start.
